race.description: Evergreen Turf David Bourke Memorial Hcp (Bm84)
race.comment: MADIYYA (12) is the horse with upside who could end up in better races. She was a drifter first up in betting at Cranbourne and just got way too far back on the fast track. Her late splits said she ran better than the 5th of 8 would suggest. Her form last time in was very progressive and getting to 1600m now is ideal. She'll likely get back again but Pakenham will suit her much better. FARHH FLUNG (1) is ultra-consistent, trying hard out to 1800m at Flemington two back, good again in a leader-dominated Kilmore Cup latest. He should be right there again. WAIMARIE (2) bounced back to form last week with a good win at Ballarat. Want to see how that form translates as plenty didn't run to expectations. NATION'S CALL (8) can mix form but is going okay and looks suited kicking up to lead without much pressure. HIYAAM PROUD (11) might look to roll forward from a wide gate and has claims if so.
